id: pm-55ra
title: "Token-budget context packer: diversity-aware selection, projection degradation, and bounded output for pm context/next"
description: "Turn ranked candidates into the most useful bounded-token context packet, shrinking projections before dropping relevant work."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: context,relevance,scale,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:50:39.960Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T20:19:42.180Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-13T19:56:00.971Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 360
acceptance_criteria: "pm context and pm next accept or derive an explicit token budget; packer preserves high-scoring required items, avoids near-duplicate context clusters, degrades projection depth before item omission, and reports budget accounting in json/debug output; behavior is measured by pm-cu1i token corpus and pm-atfm quality judgments; large-workspace output remains bounded by contract."
parent: pm-4k6b
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: Delivered reusable intent-profiled token and latency budget packing primitives shared by pm context and pm next.
expected_result: "Relevant required and diverse items remain inside explicit bounded packets, degrading projection before omission with transparent accounting."
actual_result: "Public SDK packer, CLI integration, latency certificate, five-scenario quality corpus, 10k scale proof, packed consumer, and exact 100% coverage all pass."
