comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T23:50:39.960Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for token budget packer/projection degradation/context ranking; existing items cover token measurement and pagination, but no packer implementation item existed."
  "2026-07-13T18:17:04.538Z",codex-root,"Progress evidence: SDK-first packer, context/next integration, projection accounting, diversity and uncertainty handling, focused 79-test suite green."
  "2026-07-13T19:55:48.657Z",codex-root,"Completion evidence: delivered public SDK packing profiles and deterministic token-budget selection with required-anchor immunity, cluster/lineage diversity, risk-adjusted uncertainty, identity-summary-full projection degradation, 25 ms bounded selection, and disclosed token/latency/completeness accounting shared by context and next. Exact full suite passes 281 files / 5,623 tests at 100% statements 35,768/35,768, branches 25,652/25,652, functions 7,233/7,233, lines 34,965/34,965. The 10,000-item scale gate passes its p95<1000 ms and <=5000 token product contract; five-scenario context quality is 1.0 on every aggregate metric; lint, zero-clone, static/docstring, package-boundary, token-budget, docs-links, contracts, security, and pnpm audit gates pass. Fresh manual CLI acceptance at /tmp/pm-context-acceptance-iIdToh observed serves=2, touches=3, disabled_lines=5; packed external SDK acceptance at /tmp/pm-sdk-pack-acceptance-rVOANR imported the tarball and exercised full projection plus batch feedback. Package-first dogfood passed 88 commands."
  "2026-07-13T20:19:42.180Z",codex-root,"Review convergence evidence: Gemini optimization findings accepted: the 10k-scale selector now checks its monotonic clock once per 128 candidates, projection upgrades use an id tie-breaker, and token estimates reuse one module TextEncoder. Greptile default-author mismatch fixed by resolving settings.author_default at the central post-command boundary. Exact post-fix suite: 281 files, 5,625 tests, 35,780/35,780 statements, 25,666/25,666 branches, 7,236/7,236 functions, 34,975/34,975 lines. Lint, zero clones, static/docstring, package boundary, token budget, five-scenario context evaluation, and 88-command package-first dogfood all pass."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-12T19:07:34.082Z",maintainer-agent,"Scope addition 2026-07-12 (pm-4k6b algorithms (18)+(19), definitions on that ledger): the packer surface owns (a) the explicit latency-budget parameter with threshold-algorithm early termination and a disclosed completeness certificate + degradation ladder in the envelope (algorithm 18), and (b) the task-set profile table keyed by triggering intent, with active-profile disclosure and safety-signal mask-immunity (algorithm 19). Learned-profile graduation is pm-uwfs (wave 4), not here."
  "2026-07-13T17:50:53.366Z",maintainer-agent,"Packer hooks from pm-4k6b directed pass 2026-07-13 (additions to this item's existing (18) deadline contract + (19) profile table ownership): (a) algorithm (21) risk-adjusted marginal value — packing consumes each estimate's credible width, value = mean - lambda*sigma with lambda selectable per (19) profile, so uncertain high-scorers can enter at reduced projection instead of full verbatim; --explain-ranking discloses the evidence basis (n, raw, shrunk, prior). (b) algorithm (22) lineage dedupe — lineage-mates count as near-duplicates in the (4) redundancy penalty; only the best chain representative spends budget, carrying a lineage breadcrumb for drill-down. Definitions in the pm-4k6b ledger, algorithms (21)-(22)."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T19:55:47.329Z",codex-root,"A token-bounded selector needs two separate completeness concepts: projection completeness (everything fit at full detail) and search completeness (the latency budget allowed every candidate comparison). Disclosing both prevents a fast degraded packet from masquerading as an exact optimum."
